<HEADLINE> GTE Sells Airfone Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- The manufacturer of a widely used in-air  
telephone will be sold to private equity investment firm, parent 
corporation GTE Corp. announced. 
</P>
<P>
	GTE will sell its in-flight communications unit, GTE Airfone, to  
Oak Hill Capital Partners LP. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal, announced Thursday, were not disclosed. GTE  
said the deal is expected to close in the third quarter, pending 
approval by federal regulators. 
</P>
<P>
	According to GTE, Airfone provides in-flight telephone and data  
communications to 61 percent of North American commercial aircraft. 
The phones are usually mounted in the rear of airplane seats. 
</P>
<P>
	GTE, with 1998 revenues of about $25.5 billion, is a  
telecommunications company. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
