<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 132.03  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks tumbled again under the burden of higher  
interest rates, but investors today found an added catalyst for a 
selloff: scattered warnings of weakness in second-quarter earnings. 
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 132.03 at 10,534.83, 
the fourth straight decline for the blue-chip index. Broader stock 
indicators also fell, with the Nasdaq composite index down 44.04 at 
2,554.08. While most analysts expect a robust reporting season when 
the second quarter ends next week, early indications of trouble 
sent stocks spiraling lower today. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
