<HEADLINE> Brewers' De Los Santos Has Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Milwaukee Brewers reliever Valerio De Los  
Santos had surgery to remove a protruding disk from his lower back 
and is expected to make a full recovery, the team said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	De Los Santos, 23, has been on the disabled list since April  
after starting the season 0-1 with an 8.53 ERA in five relief 
appearances. 
</P>
<P>
	Wednesday's 2-hour operation by Dr. Spencer Block at St. Michael  
Hospital was to relieve back pain caused by the disk pressing on 
nerves of the lower back. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no timetable set for De Los Santos' return.  
  	   	
