through with a successful sequel to her upset of Martina Hingis, 
edging Katarina Studenikova 6-0, 4-6, 8-6 at Wimbledon today. Andre 
Agassi, still riding the momentum of his French Open triumph, swept 
Guillermo Canas 6-3, 6-4, 6-3. Agassi, seeded fourth, has lost just 
16 games in his first two matches. No. 7 Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario 
joined Hingis as the only seeded women on the sidelines, losing to 
Lisa Raymond 7-6 (7-4), 6-1. 

</P>
