<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tigers Put Jefferies on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Gregg Jefferies was placed on the 15-day  
disabled list by the Detroit Tigers on Thursday because of a 
bruised right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Jefferies, a 31-year-old outfielder and designated hitter, was  
injured Saturday when he was hit by a pitch from Oakland's Tim 
Hudson. He is batting .211 with five homers and 16 RBIs in 54 games 
this season. The roster moved was made retroactive to Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Detroit recalled infielder Jose Macias from Triple-A Toledo.  
Macias, 25, was brought up May 7 and appeared in four games. He had 
four at-bats, hitting one home run, and was sent back to Toledo on 
May 21. 
  	   	
</P>
