<DOCNO> APW19990624.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 15:50:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Morgan Stanley Earnings Up 35 Pct. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Morgan Stanley Dean Witter &AMP; Co. reported  
Thursday it earned $1.15 billion in the second quarter of its 
fiscal year, handily beating analysts' estimates and marking a 35 
percent increase over the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	The big investment firm attributed the strong showing to healthy  
results across the broad range of its businesses, including equity 
underwriting, merger transactions, and overseas operations. 
</P>
<P>
	The earnings were equivalent to $1.95 per share in the quarter  
ended May 31, easily surpassing the $1.54 per share expected by 
analysts surveyed by First Call Corp. In the same period a year 
ago, the company earned $852 million, or $1.37 per share. 
</P>
<P>
	Revenues, not including interest expenses and provisions for  
loan losses, rose 23 percent to $5.66 billion from $4.60 billion a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Morgan Stanley joined rivals Lehman Brothers and Goldman Sachs  
in announcing strong earnings for the second quarter. But the 
company's stock fell $1.31 a share to $91.31 in New York Stock 
Exchange trading Thursday as investors grew increasingly uneasy 
about interest rates in advance of next week's meeting of the 
Federal Reserve Board's Open Market Committee. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors, while already expecting rates to go up at that  
meeting, are concerned that Morgan Stanley and other financial 
companies will see their earnings decline if the Fed undertakes a 
series of rate hikes over the next few months. 
</P>
<P>
	During the second quarter, Morgan Stanley's earnings from  
trading, selling and underwriting securities -- which makes up the 
vast majority of the firm's business -- soared 54 percent thanks to 
a strong showing in European and Asian markets, underwriting stock 
and handling mergers. 
</P>
<P>
	The company's online Discover Brokerage Direct reported a 78  
percent jump in trading volume during the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	For the first six months of its fiscal year, Morgan Stanley  
earned $2.19 billion or $3.71 per share, compared to $1.54 billion 
or $2.47 per share in the same period a year ago. Revenues rose 27 
percent to $11 billion from $8.63 billion. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
