<HEADLINE> Garciaparra Sidelined by Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Boston Red Sox shortstop Nomar Garciaparra  
could be sidelined for several days by a strained leg muscle, 
although he insists the injury will not force him onto the disabled 
list. 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra strained his left quad running out a ninth-inning  
triple Tuesday night in Boston's 5-0 victory over the Baltimore 
Orioles. The injury occurred as he was rounding first base. 
</P>
<P>
	He did not start Thursday night, but manager Jimy Williams said  
the player was available as a pinch hitter. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know how serious it is yet. Hopefully we won't need  
him tonight,'' Williams said Thursday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra has an 11-game hitting streak, going 21-for-38  
during the span. He has 13 hits in his last 18 at-bats, and can't 
wait to get back in the lineup. 
</P>
<P>
	``It won't be a DL thing. That's for sure,'' he said. ``I won't  
let it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra missed 19 games last year and nine in 1997. He was  
replaced in the starting lineup Thursday by Lou Merloni. 
  	   	
</P>
