<HEADLINE> Dollar Down Vs. Euro, Others </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar fell against the euro and other major  
currencies Thursday ahead of a meeting of the Fed's interest rate 
board next week. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the euro was quoted at $1.0397, up  
from $1.0330 late Wednesday. The dollar also was quoted at 121.78 
Japanese yen, down from 121.92 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar followed stocks and bonds lower Thursday as fears  
that the Fed will raise interest rates at its meeting next Tuesday 
cast a pall over U.S. financial markets. Bonds and stocks have been 
declining all week after Fed chairman Alan Greenspan hinted last 
week that rates could be heading higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.5336 Swiss francs, down from  
1.5469, and 1.4722 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4716. The British 
pound rose to $1.5888 from $1.5795. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
Based on Thursday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8811 German 
marks, down from 1.8933; 6.3091 French francs, down from 6.3500; 
and 1,862.20 Italian lire, down from 1,876.23. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
