<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Twins Agree to Terms With Top Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- The Minnesota Twins agreed Thursday to a  
minor league contract with center fielder B.J. Garbe, their fifth 
pick in this month's amateur draft. 
</P>
<P>
	The 18-year-old hit .500 this season for Moses Lake High School  
in Washington with five doubles, three triples, six homers and 22 
RBIs. He stole 19 bases and led Moses Lake to a 23-2 record and the 
semifinals of the Washington state Class AAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Garbe will report to the Elizabethton Twins of the Appalachian  
League on July 8. 
</P>
<P>
	As part of the agreement, Garbe will set up an athletic  
scholarship at Moses Lake High School and donate $10,000 to the 
Columbia Basin River Dogs, his summer Senior Babe Ruth team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
