<HEADLINE> Ex-Cub Santo in Chicago Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Chicago Cubs radio commentator and former player  
Ron Santo returned to Chicago on Thursday and is receiving further 
treatment at Northwestern Memorial Hospital for a mild heart 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
	Cubs spokesman Javier Bedolla said Santo checked out of Denver's  
Rose Medical Center, but did not know Santo's condition. The 
hospital declined to release any information. 
</P>
<P>
	Santo, 59, a nine-time All-Star third baseman, admitted himself  
to Rose Medical Center on Monday after experiencing chest pains in 
his hotel room. He later showed improvement and was given 
medication for abnormalities in his heart's rhythm. 
</P>
<P>
	Santo, a five-time Gold Glove winner with the Cubs, became the  
team's radio announcer 10 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Santo has a history of diabetes and recently underwent an  
angiogram that revealed a minor blockage of one artery. 
</P>
