<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Elderly Driver Kills Baby in Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- A 71-year-old woman who drove home on an  
expired license after flunking her driver's test struck and killed 
a baby in a stroller hours later, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman, who has not been charged, made a wide turn at a  
crosswalk, almost going up on the sidewalk, police Inspector Mike 
Mahoney said. 
</P>
<P>
	She had been issued a temporary license that expired June 18,  
Mahoney said. She failed her exam that day because she went 
straight when the instructor told her to turn left. 
</P>
<P>
	The Department of Motor Vehicles instructor told the woman that  
she had failed and would have to return. The instructor did not 
specifically tell the woman she could not drive home, Mahoney said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Nonetheless, the woman drove home and parked her car, then went  
to move it to a different spot about five hours later. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten-month-old Yusuf Khouja was dragged in his stroller beneath  
the car and later died at a hospital. His 2 1/2-year-old brother 
suffered minor injuries. Their mother was not hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver told investigators that her brakes failed, Mahoney  
said. A mechanical inspection was being done Thursday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
