<HEADLINE> 2 Special Olympics Athletes Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Police searched Thursday for two Special  
Olympics basketball players from the Dominican Republic who 
apparently slipped away during a group outing, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Maximo Martinez, 21, and Jose Gallardo, 20, were reported  
missing Wednesday during a trip to a shopping mall with 21 other 
athletes. A cab driver reported taking two men matching their 
description to the bus station in Charlotte 80 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
	The two apparently had planned the getaway by devising a way to  
conceal from chaperones that they were in possession of their 
passports, police Capt. Jim Scifres said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police were following a lead Thursday night that the two had  
gone to New York state. 
</P>
<P>
	Greensboro was the Dominican Republic delegation's host town for  
the Special Olympics, which begin Saturday and end July 4. Special 
Olympics officials wouldn't comment and referred questions to 
police. 
  	   	
</P>
