<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Women's World Cup Notebook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Ever since David Letterman had defender Brandi Chastain on the  
show two weeks ago, ``The Late Show'' host has been an on-air 
supporter for the U.S. women's team. Letterman talks about the 
team's exploits in his show and there's even a rumor of a Letterman 
producer following the team. 
</P>
<P>
	The team is reveling in the attention, watching Letterman's show  
and wearing the T-shirts Letterman gave Chastain to give to her 
teammates. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's having a lot of fun with the tournament and the team,''  
said U.S. coach Tony DiCicco. ``It looks like they want to do 
something more with us during the event, but as much as I would 
like to meet David Letterman, we still have to stay focused on 
winning games.'' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *SHALALA AT GAMES:* Donna Shalala, the Secretary of Health and  
Human Services Department, will visit two World Cup games played in 
Jack Kent Cooke Stadium near Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Shalala will be watching the first- round doubleheader as  
Germany meets Brazil and Nigeria faces Denmark on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The second match Shalala will attend will be on July 1 in the  
quarterfinals. It's unclear which teams will be playing, but it is 
likely the United States will be in that doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *THIRD HAT TRICK:* China captain Sun Wen scored the third hat  
trick of the tournament in a 7-0 win over Ghana on Wednesday. Sun 
put the Chinese on track with her first goal in the ninth minute. 
She scored again in the 20th minute, giving China 3-0 lead going 
into halftime. In the 54th minute, Sun got her third goal when she 
grabbed a missed shot off the crossbar and left-footed it into the 
top of the net for a 4-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	In the last minutes of the game, the Chinese dominated Ghana,  
scoring another three goals. 
</P>
<P>
	``The team's fighting spirit was the one thing that helped us  
win the game,'' Sun said. 
</P>
<P>
	The other two hat tricks of the tournament were scored by  
Brazil's Pretinha and Sissi, who each scored three goals in a 7-1 
win over Mexico last Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *THE NAKED TRUTH:* After a revealing photograph of defender  
Brandi Chastain appeared in a recent issue of Gear magazine, coach 
Tony DiCicco wasn't worried about the image of the United States 
women's team. Chastain was shown in a side shot wearing nothing but 
a strategically placed soccer ball at her chest. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think it was interesting,'' said DiCicco. ``You've got to  
know Brandi. Brandi's got as big a heart as anyone on this team and 
she'd never do anything to undermine how this team is viewed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	DiCicco added he didn't think the picture was a blemish on the  
team's image. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think she kept it in a context that did promote women as  
fit, athletic, strong and still beautiful,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The picture did get Chastain some media exposure. David  
Letterman invited her to his show and showed the picture on the 
air. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
