<HEADLINE> Nancy Lopez Has Successful Surgery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) -- Nancy Lopez had arthroscopic surgery  
Thursday morning to remove torn cartilage from her right knee, and 
is expected to be out for about a month. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Craig Morgan of the Morgan Kalman Clinic said the procedure  
took 25 minutes and went according to schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	Lopez is expected to stay in the hospital until Saturday before  
returning home to Albany, Ga. 
</P>
<P>
	She was in tears Wednesday afternoon when she announced she  
would have to withdraw from the LPGA Championship, which she has 
won three times. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not anything major,'' she said. ``Besides being  
disappointed, I'm fine.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Defending champion Se Ri Pak, who opened with a 68, said she was  
going to visit Lopez in the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Pak was paired with Lopez in the first two rounds last year, and  
Lopez immediately took an interest in the 21-year-old South Korean. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm pretty sad, too,'' Pak said. ``I wanted to see her this  
week. We talked about this week, if we can have practice round 
together. But she started with pain in the knee, so that was kind 
of sad. But I hope she will feel better.'' 
  	   	
