<HEADLINE> Religion Briefs / Religion Briefs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLES CITY, Iowa (AP) -- St. John Evangelical Lutheran Church  
is offering more than prayers to protect children. It is offering 
trigger locks that prevent a gun from firing. 
</P>
<P>
	``Our goal here is to keep children safe. And what can be more  
appropriate for a church to be doing?'' said Mark Anderson, St. 
John's pastor. 
</P>
<P>
	Teen-agers from the church were to hand out the locks at a  
shopping mall, show how to install them and talk about gun safety. 
</P>
<P>
	In the aftermath of the Columbine High School killings in  
Colorado, Anderson said, ``a debate on national gun control policy 
is not as effective as handing out trigger locks. You can go home 
and say there are 100 guns out there that are safer.'' 
</P>
