<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Craig McCaw To Invest in Nextel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KIRKLAND, Wash. (AP) -- Craig McCaw, his family and ex-wife plan  
to exercise options for 17 million shares in Nextel Communications, 
investing about $315 million more in the wireless calling company. 
</P>
<P>
	The McCaws originally agreed to invest up to $1.16 billion in  
Nextel in 1995. The options they plan to exercise are part of that 
purchase agreement. 
</P>
<P>
	Afterwards, Craig McCaw plans to reduce his holdings by about 7  
percent of his Nextel shares through an independent trustee, 
selling 15,000 shares on each of the next 200 trading days, 
regardless of the price. 
</P>
<P>
	McCaw is the founder of McCaw Cellular, which was sold to AT&AMP;T  
in 1994 for $11.5 billion. He sits on Nextel's board of directors 
and is chairman of the company's operating committee. He is also 
the founder and a director of NextLink Communications Inc. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
