<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 15:04:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  1 Dead, 21 Hurt in French Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- One person was killed and 21 injured when a bus  
carrying American and French schoolchildren struck a tree Thursday 
morning while on a field trip to Paris. Seven Americans aged 10-11 
from the Grand Rapids, Mich., area were among the injured. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver, who was killed instantly, lost control of the bus in  
Orconte, about 115 miles east of Paris. 
</P>
<P>
	Twenty-one children suffered facial and leg injures but none  
were considered life-threatening, police and doctors said. 
Twenty-six other children on the bus suffered minor bruises. 
</P>
<P>
	The children not requiring surgery were expected to leave the  
hospital late Thursday or early Friday, doctors said. A French 
adult accompanying the young people suffered head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	None of the victims were identified.  
</P>
<P>
	French authorities sent psychologists to speak with the children  
at the crash site and in the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The American students arrived in France on June 10th as part of  
a three-week exchange program coordinated by the French-American 
Association of Epinal, a town about 250 miles east of Paris. 
</P>
<P>
	The schoolchildren were on their way to Paris for a two-day  
field trip when the accident occurred. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the American children live in the Forest Hills School  
District in suburban Grand Rapids, said Forest Hills spokeswoman 
Karen Lott. She said the trip was privately sponsored and not 
connected to the district. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. consular officials were on their way to provide assistance  
to the victims and to contact the parents. Some children had been 
put in contact with their parents by telephone. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990624.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 15:04:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  1 Dead, 21 Hurt in French Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- One person was killed and 21 injured when a bus  
carrying American and French schoolchildren struck a tree Thursday 
morning while on a field trip to Paris. Seven Americans aged 10-11 
from the Grand Rapids, Mich., area were among the injured. 
</P>
