<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crier Leaving Fox News for Court TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Judge-turned-newswoman Catherine Crier is  
leaving the Fox News Channel for Court TV, where she will anchor a 
midday legal news show. 
</P>
<P>
	Crier's show, which begins this fall, will offer commentary and  
analysis of ``front page'' legal news stories, Court TV said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Crier has been anchoring Fox's ``The Crier Report,'' a nightly  
live news program for which she interviewed top newsmakers of the 
day. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was exciting to be part of the dynamic launch of Fox News  
Channel, and I have enjoyed my three years here, but my first love 
is the law,'' she said. ``I am looking forward to being a part of a 
cable operation geared towards reaching those who are as passionate 
about the law as I am.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Trained as a lawyer, Crier became a state district court judge  
in Dallas in 1984 at age 30 -- the youngest state judge in Texas 
history -- and served for five years. 
</P>
<P>
	She joined CNN in 1989 and later worked at ABC.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
