<HEADLINE> Bridget Fonda Suffered Stage Fright </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Even though she is from a show business family,  
Bridget Fonda says she was paralyzed by stage fright early in her 
career. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd go on stage, and later I couldn't remember a thing I'd  
done,'' the actress, who has been in more than 30 movies, said in 
this Sunday's Parade magazine. ``I'd think, `I'm the worst person 
in the class.' They all looked at me like I should know better 
because of my heritage.'' 
</P>
<P>
	So how did the daughter of Peter Fonda and granddaughter of  
Henry Fonda overcome her fear? 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm stubborn,'' she said. ``I've learned that when it's  
something you care about, you have to take chances.'' 
</P>
<P>
